    <div class="page-intro">
      <h1>Use of English (Use of English / English Language)</h1>
      <p class="muted">JAMB Use of English syllabus: comprehension, summary, lexis & structure, and oral forms.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="page-intro-actions" style="display:flex;gap:12px;align-items:center;margin-top:8px;flex-wrap:wrap;">
      <a href="#" class="btn-outline">Download PDF</a>
      <a href="../JambSyllabus.htm" class="btn-outline">← Back to All Subjects</a>
    </div>

    <!-- Syllabus table: each major syllabus section is a row with recommended textbooks and OAE notes -->
    <div class="syllabus-table-wrap" style="overflow:auto;">
      <table class="syllabus-table" style="width:100%;border-collapse:collapse;min-width:860px;">
        <thead>
          <tr style="background:#f3fff3;">
            <th style="padding:12px;border:1px solid #e6e6e6;text-align:left;">Section</th>
            <th style="padding:12px;border:1px solid #e6e6e6;text-align:left;">Topics / Focus</th>
            <th style="padding:12px;border:1px solid #e6e6e6;text-align:left;">Details / Objectives</th>
            <th style="padding:12px;border:1px solid #e6e6e6;text-align:left;">Recommended Textbooks (selected)</th>
            <th style="padding:12px;border:1px solid #e6e6e6;text-align:left;">OAE Notes</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <!-- SECTION A: Comprehension & Summary -->
          <tr style="background:#2d5a3d;color:white;">
            <td colspan="5" style="padding:14px;border:1px solid #1a3a24;font-weight:bold;font-size:16px;text-align:left;">
              📖 SECTION A — Comprehension & Summary
            </td>
          </tr>
          <tr style="background:#f9fdf9;">
            <td style="padding:12px;border:1px solid #ddd;vertical-align:top;font-weight:bold;">A.1</td>
            <td style="padding:12px;border:1px solid #ddd;vertical-align:top;">Description</td>
            <td style="padding:12px;border:1px solid #ddd;vertical-align:top;">Identify details, sensory description, organisation of descriptive passages.</td>
            <td style="padding:12px;border:1px solid #ddd;vertical-align:top;">—</td>
            <td style="padding:12px;border:1px solid #ddd;vertical-align:middle;text-align:center;"><a href="notes/english/comprehension-summary.htm" style="color:#2c5aa0;font-weight:bold;">Check notes</a></td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td style="padding:12px;border:1px solid #ddd;vertical-align:top;font-weight:bold;">A.2</td>
            <td style="padding:12px;border:1px solid #ddd;vertical-align:top;">Narration</td>
            <td style="padding:12px;border:1px solid #ddd;vertical-align:top;">Sequence of events, viewpoint, tense choice and narrative cohesion.</td>
            <td style="padding:12px;border:1px solid #ddd;vertical-align:top;">—</td>
            <td style="padding:12px;border:1px solid #ddd;vertical-align:middle;text-align:center;"><a href="notes/english/comprehension-summary.htm" style="color:#2c5aa0;font-weight:bold;">Check notes</a></td>
          </tr>
          <tr style="background:#f9fdf9;">
            <td style="padding:12px;border:1px solid #ddd;vertical-align:top;font-weight:bold;">A.3</td>
            <td style="padding:12px;border:1px solid #ddd;vertical-align:top;">Exposition</td>
            <td style="padding:12px;border:1px solid #ddd;vertical-align:top;">Explanation and logical organisation; thesis and supporting points.</td>
            <td style="padding:12px;border:1px solid #ddd;vertical-align:top;">—</td>
            <td style="padding:12px;border:1px solid #ddd;vertical-align:middle;text-align:center;"><a href="notes/english/comprehension-summary.htm" style="color:#2c5aa0;font-weight:bold;">Check notes</a></td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td style="padding:12px;border:1px solid #ddd;vertical-align:top;font-weight:bold;">A.4</td>
            <td style="padding:12px;border:1px solid #ddd;vertical-align:top;">Argumentation / Persuasion</td>
            <td style="padding:12px;border:1px solid #ddd;vertical-align:top;">Recognise claims, evidence and persuasive strategies; evaluate argument strength.</td>
            <td style="padding:12px;border:1px solid #ddd;vertical-align:top;">—</td>
            <td style="padding:12px;border:1px solid #ddd;vertical-align:middle;text-align:center;"><a href="notes/english/comprehension-summary.htm" style="color:#2c5aa0;font-weight:bold;">Check notes</a></td>
          </tr>
          <tr style="background:#f9fdf9;">
            <td style="padding:12px;border:1px solid #ddd;vertical-align:top;font-weight:bold;">A.5</td>
            <td style="padding:12px;border:1px solid #ddd;vertical-align:top;">Main idea & supporting ideas</td>
            <td style="padding:12px;border:1px solid #ddd;vertical-align:top;">Find thesis statements and supporting evidence; summarise accurately.</td>
            <td style="padding:12px;border:1px solid #ddd;vertical-align:top;">—</td>
            <td style="padding:12px;border:1px solid #ddd;vertical-align:middle;text-align:center;"><a href="notes/english/comprehension-summary.htm" style="color:#2c5aa0;font-weight:bold;">Check notes</a></td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td style="padding:12px;border:1px solid #ddd;vertical-align:top;font-weight:bold;">A.6</td>
            <td style="padding:12px;border:1px solid #ddd;vertical-align:top;">Tone, mood & attitude</td>
            <td style="padding:12px;border:1px solid #ddd;vertical-align:top;">Identify writer's tone, bias, irony and attitude through diction and structure.</td>
            <td style="padding:12px;border:1px solid #ddd;vertical-align:top;">—</td>
            <td style="padding:12px;border:1px solid #ddd;vertical-align:middle;text-align:center;"><a href="notes/english/comprehension-summary.htm" style="color:#2c5aa0;font-weight:bold;">Check notes</a></td>
          </tr>
          <tr style="background:#f9fdf9;">
            <td style="padding:12px;border:1px solid #ddd;vertical-align:top;font-weight:bold;">A.7</td>
            <td style="padding:12px;border:1px solid #ddd;vertical-align:top;">Contextual meaning & vocabulary</td>
            <td style="padding:12px;border:1px solid #ddd;vertical-align:top;">Use context clues to determine word meaning and register; paraphrase.</td>
            <td style="padding:12px;border:1px solid #ddd;vertical-align:top;">—</td>
            <td style="padding:12px;border:1px solid #ddd;vertical-align:middle;text-align:center;"><a href="notes/english/comprehension-summary.htm" style="color:#2c5aa0;font-weight:bold;">Check notes</a></td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td style="padding:12px;border:1px solid #ddd;vertical-align:top;font-weight:bold;">A.8</td>
            <td style="padding:12px;border:1px solid #ddd;vertical-align:top;">Inference & deduction</td>
            <td style="padding:12px;border:1px solid #ddd;vertical-align:top;">Draw logical conclusions from implied statements and evidence.</td>
            <td style="padding:12px;border:1px solid #ddd;vertical-align:top;">—</td>
            <td style="padding:12px;border:1px solid #ddd;vertical-align:middle;text-align:center;"><a href="notes/english/comprehension-summary.htm" style="color:#2c5aa0;font-weight:bold;">Check notes</a></td>
          </tr>
          <tr style="background:#f9fdf9;">
            <td style="padding:12px;border:1px solid #ddd;vertical-align:top;font-weight:bold;">A.9</td>
            <td style="padding:12px;border:1px solid #ddd;vertical-align:top;">Figures of speech</td>
            <td style="padding:12px;border:1px solid #ddd;vertical-align:top;">Identify and interpret metaphor, simile, irony, hyperbole, etc.</td>
            <td style="padding:12px;border:1px solid #ddd;vertical-align:top;">—</td>
            <td style="padding:12px;border:1px solid #ddd;vertical-align:middle;text-align:center;"><a href="notes/english/lexis-structure.htm" style="color:#2c5aa0;font-weight:bold;">Check notes</a></td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td style="padding:12px;border:1px solid #ddd;vertical-align:top;font-weight:bold;">A.10</td>
            <td style="padding:12px;border:1px solid #ddd;vertical-align:top;">Sentence & paragraph coherence</td>
            <td style="padding:12px;border:1px solid #ddd;vertical-align:top;">Recognise cohesion devices and paragraphing for logical flow.</td>
            <td style="padding:12px;border:1px solid #ddd;vertical-align:top;">—</td>
            <td style="padding:12px;border:1px solid #ddd;vertical-align:middle;text-align:center;"><a href="notes/english/comprehension-summary.htm" style="color:#2c5aa0;font-weight:bold;">Check notes</a></td>
          </tr>
          <tr style="background:#f9fdf9;">
            <td style="padding:12px;border:1px solid #ddd;vertical-align:top;font-weight:bold;">A.11</td>
            <td style="padding:12px;border:1px solid #ddd;vertical-align:top;">Idiomatic expressions & proverbs</td>
            <td style="padding:12px;border:1px solid #ddd;vertical-align:top;">Interpret idioms and proverbs in context; note connotation.</td>
            <td style="padding:12px;border:1px solid #ddd;vertical-align:top;">—</td>
            <td style="padding:12px;border:1px solid #ddd;vertical-align:middle;text-align:center;"><a href="notes/english/lexis-structure.htm" style="color:#2c5aa0;font-weight:bold;">Check notes</a></td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td style="padding:12px;border:1px solid #ddd;vertical-align:top;font-weight:bold;">A.12</td>
            <td style="padding:12px;border:1px solid #ddd;vertical-align:top;">Cloze tests</td>
            <td style="padding:12px;border:1px solid #ddd;vertical-align:top;">Strategies for missing-word selection: collocations, grammar, sense, register.</td>
            <td style="padding:12px;border:1px solid #ddd;vertical-align:top;">—</td>
            <td style="padding:12px;border:1px solid #ddd;vertical-align:middle;text-align:center;"><a href="notes/english/cloze.htm" style="color:#2c5aa0;font-weight:bold;">Check notes</a></td>
          </tr>
          <tr style="background:#f9fdf9;">
            <td style="padding:12px;border:1px solid #ddd;vertical-align:top;font-weight:bold;">A.13</td>
            <td style="padding:12px;border:1px solid #ddd;vertical-align:top;">Summary writing</td>
            <td style="padding:12px;border:1px solid #ddd;vertical-align:top;">Identify main ideas and paraphrase concisely; observe word limits.</td>
            <td style="padding:12px;border:1px solid #ddd;vertical-align:top;">—</td>
            <td style="padding:12px;border:1px solid #ddd;vertical-align:middle;text-align:center;"><a href="notes/english/summary-writing.htm" style="color:#2c5aa0;font-weight:bold;">Check notes</a></td>
          </tr>

          <!-- SECTION B: Lexis & Structure -->
          <tr style="background:#2d5a3d;color:white;">
            <td colspan="5" style="padding:14px;border:1px solid #1a3a24;font-weight:bold;font-size:16px;text-align:left;">
              ✏️ SECTION B — Lexis & Structure
            </td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td style="padding:12px;border:1px solid #ddd;vertical-align:top;font-weight:bold;">B.1</td>
            <td style="padding:12px;border:1px solid #ddd;vertical-align:top;">Synonyms</td>
            <td style="padding:12px;border:1px solid #ddd;vertical-align:top;">Select words with matching meaning and register; consider collocation.</td>
            <td style="padding:12px;border:1px solid #ddd;vertical-align:top;">Bamgbose (Lexis & Structure)</td>
            <td style="padding:12px;border:1px solid #ddd;vertical-align:middle;text-align:center;"><a href="notes/english/synonyms.htm" style="color:#2c5aa0;font-weight:bold;">Check notes</a></td>
          </tr>
          <tr style="background:#f9fdf9;">
            <td style="padding:12px;border:1px solid #ddd;vertical-align:top;font-weight:bold;">B.2</td>
            <td style="padding:12px;border:1px solid #ddd;vertical-align:top;">Antonyms</td>
            <td style="padding:12px;border:1px solid #ddd;vertical-align:top;">Choose opposites appropriate to context; gradable vs binary opposites.</td>
            <td style="padding:12px;border:1px solid #ddd;vertical-align:top;">—</td>
            <td style="padding:12px;border:1px solid #ddd;vertical-align:middle;text-align:center;"><a href="notes/english/antonyms.htm" style="color:#2c5aa0;font-weight:bold;">Check notes</a></td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td style="padding:12px;border:1px solid #ddd;vertical-align:top;font-weight:bold;">B.3</td>
            <td style="padding:12px;border:1px solid #ddd;vertical-align:top;">Homonyms</td>
            <td style="padding:12px;border:1px solid #ddd;vertical-align:top;">Distinguish same spelling/pronunciation but different meanings from context.</td>
            <td style="padding:12px;border:1px solid #ddd;vertical-align:top;">—</td>
            <td style="padding:12px;border:1px solid #ddd;vertical-align:middle;text-align:center;"><a href="notes/english/lexis-structure.htm" style="color:#2c5aa0;font-weight:bold;">Check notes</a></td>
          </tr>
          <tr style="background:#f9fdf9;">
            <td style="padding:12px;border:1px solid #ddd;vertical-align:top;font-weight:bold;">B.4</td>
            <td style="padding:12px;border:1px solid #ddd;vertical-align:top;">Word formation</td>
            <td style="padding:12px;border:1px solid #ddd;vertical-align:top;">Study prefixes, suffixes, roots, compounding and conversion to guess meanings.</td>
            <td style="padding:12px;border:1px solid #ddd;vertical-align:top;">—</td>
            <td style="padding:12px;border:1px solid #ddd;vertical-align:middle;text-align:center;"><a href="notes/english/word-formation.htm" style="color:#2c5aa0;font-weight:bold;">Check notes</a></td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td style="padding:12px;border:1px solid #ddd;vertical-align:top;font-weight:bold;">B.5</td>
            <td style="padding:12px;border:1px solid #ddd;vertical-align:top;">Idiomatic expressions & figurative language</td>
            <td style="padding:12px;border:1px solid #ddd;vertical-align:top;">Recognise idioms, metaphors and figurative uses; interpret in context.</td>
            <td style="padding:12px;border:1px solid #ddd;vertical-align:top;">—</td>
            <td style="padding:12px;border:1px solid #ddd;vertical-align:middle;text-align:center;"><a href="notes/english/lexis-structure.htm" style="color:#2c5aa0;font-weight:bold;">Check notes</a></td>
          </tr>
          <tr style="background:#f9fdf9;">
            <td style="padding:12px;border:1px solid #ddd;vertical-align:top;font-weight:bold;">B.6</td>
            <td style="padding:12px;border:1px solid #ddd;vertical-align:top;">Collocations & phrasal verbs</td>
            <td style="padding:12px;border:1px solid #ddd;vertical-align:top;">Learn common word partners and multi-word verbs for accurate usage.</td>
            <td style="padding:12px;border:1px solid #ddd;vertical-align:top;">—</td>
            <td style="padding:12px;border:1px solid #ddd;vertical-align:middle;text-align:center;"><a href="notes/english/lexis-structure.htm" style="color:#2c5aa0;font-weight:bold;">Check notes</a></td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td style="padding:12px;border:1px solid #ddd;vertical-align:top;font-weight:bold;">B.7</td>
            <td style="padding:12px;border:1px solid #ddd;vertical-align:top;">Clauses & sentence types</td>
            <td style="padding:12px;border:1px solid #ddd;vertical-align:top;">Identify simple, compound and complex sentences; clause functions.</td>
            <td style="padding:12px;border:1px solid #ddd;vertical-align:top;">—</td>
            <td style="padding:12px;border:1px solid #ddd;vertical-align:middle;text-align:center;"><a href="notes/english/lexis-structure.htm" style="color:#2c5aa0;font-weight:bold;">Check notes</a></td>
          </tr>
          <tr style="background:#f9fdf9;">
            <td style="padding:12px;border:1px solid #ddd;vertical-align:top;font-weight:bold;">B.8</td>
            <td style="padding:12px;border:1px solid #ddd;vertical-align:top;">Tenses & verb forms</td>
            <td style="padding:12px;border:1px solid #ddd;vertical-align:top;">Master simple, continuous, perfect and perfect continuous; time markers.</td>
            <td style="padding:12px;border:1px solid #ddd;vertical-align:top;">—</td>
            <td style="padding:12px;border:1px solid #ddd;vertical-align:middle;text-align:center;"><a href="notes/english/tenses.htm" style="color:#2c5aa0;font-weight:bold;">Check notes</a></td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td style="padding:12px;border:1px solid #ddd;vertical-align:top;font-weight:bold;">B.9</td>
            <td style="padding:12px;border:1px solid #ddd;vertical-align:top;">Subject–verb agreement (Concord)</td>
            <td style="padding:12px;border:1px solid #ddd;vertical-align:top;">Ensure verbs agree with subjects; watch intervening phrases.</td>
            <td style="padding:12px;border:1px solid #ddd;vertical-align:top;">—</td>
            <td style="padding:12px;border:1px solid #ddd;vertical-align:middle;text-align:center;"><a href="notes/english/concord.htm" style="color:#2c5aa0;font-weight:bold;">Check notes</a></td>
          </tr>
          <tr style="background:#f9fdf9;">
            <td style="padding:12px;border:1px solid #ddd;vertical-align:top;font-weight:bold;">B.10</td>
            <td style="padding:12px;border:1px solid #ddd;vertical-align:top;">Question tags</td>
            <td style="padding:12px;border:1px solid #ddd;vertical-align:top;">Form and use appropriate question tags matching polarity and subject.</td>
            <td style="padding:12px;border:1px solid #ddd;vertical-align:top;">—</td>
            <td style="padding:12px;border:1px solid #ddd;vertical-align:middle;text-align:center;"><a href="notes/english/lexis-structure.htm" style="color:#2c5aa0;font-weight:bold;">Check notes</a></td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td style="padding:12px;border:1px solid #ddd;vertical-align:top;font-weight:bold;">B.11</td>
            <td style="padding:12px;border:1px solid #ddd;vertical-align:top;">Punctuation & spelling</td>
            <td style="padding:12px;border:1px solid #ddd;vertical-align:top;">Apply commas, colons, semicolons, apostrophes; correct spelling.</td>
            <td style="padding:12px;border:1px solid #ddd;vertical-align:top;">—</td>
            <td style="padding:12px;border:1px solid #ddd;vertical-align:middle;text-align:center;"><a href="notes/english/punctuation.htm" style="color:#2c5aa0;font-weight:bold;">Check notes</a></td>
          </tr>
          <tr style="background:#f9fdf9;">
            <td style="padding:12px;border:1px solid #ddd;vertical-align:top;font-weight:bold;">B.12</td>
            <td style="padding:12px;border:1px solid #ddd;vertical-align:top;">Sentence completion</td>
            <td style="padding:12px;border:1px solid #ddd;vertical-align:top;">Choose options that fit grammatically and semantically; test collocations.</td>
            <td style="padding:12px;border:1px solid #ddd;vertical-align:top;">—</td>
            <td style="padding:12px;border:1px solid #ddd;vertical-align:middle;text-align:center;"><a href="notes/english/sentence-completion.htm" style="color:#2c5aa0;font-weight:bold;">Check notes</a></td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td style="padding:12px;border:1px solid #ddd;vertical-align:top;font-weight:bold;">B.13</td>
            <td style="padding:12px;border:1px solid #ddd;vertical-align:top;">Sentence transformation</td>
            <td style="padding:12px;border:1px solid #ddd;vertical-align:top;">Change sentence forms preserving meaning: passives, reported speech, etc.</td>
            <td style="padding:12px;border:1px solid #ddd;vertical-align:top;">—</td>
            <td style="padding:12px;border:1px solid #ddd;vertical-align:middle;text-align:center;"><a href="notes/english/sentence-transformation.htm" style="color:#2c5aa0;font-weight:bold;">Check notes</a></td>
          </tr>

          <!-- SECTION C: Oral Forms -->
          <tr style="background:#2d5a3d;color:white;">
            <td colspan="5" style="padding:14px;border:1px solid #1a3a24;font-weight:bold;font-size:16px;text-align:left;">
              🔊 SECTION C — Oral Forms
            </td>
          </tr>
          <tr style="background:#f9fdf9;">
            <td style="padding:12px;border:1px solid #ddd;vertical-align:top;font-weight:bold;">C.1</td>
            <td style="padding:12px;border:1px solid #ddd;vertical-align:top;">Vowels (monophthongs & diphthongs)</td>
            <td style="padding:12px;border:1px solid #ddd;vertical-align:top;">Recognise vowel qualities and length differences; practice transcription.</td>
            <td style="padding:12px;border:1px solid #ddd;vertical-align:top;">Daniel Jones (Pronouncing Dictionary)</td>
            <td style="padding:12px;border:1px solid #ddd;vertical-align:middle;text-align:center;"><a href="notes/english/phonetics.htm" style="color:#2c5aa0;font-weight:bold;">Check notes</a></td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td style="padding:12px;border:1px solid #ddd;vertical-align:top;font-weight:bold;">C.2</td>
            <td style="padding:12px;border:1px solid #ddd;vertical-align:top;">Consonants & clusters</td>
            <td style="padding:12px;border:1px solid #ddd;vertical-align:top;">Distinguish voiced/voiceless pairs; practice consonant clusters.</td>
            <td style="padding:12px;border:1px solid #ddd;vertical-align:top;">—</td>
            <td style="padding:12px;border:1px solid #ddd;vertical-align:middle;text-align:center;"><a href="notes/english/phonetics.htm" style="color:#2c5aa0;font-weight:bold;">Check notes</a></td>
          </tr>
          <tr style="background:#f9fdf9;">
            <td style="padding:12px;border:1px solid #ddd;vertical-align:top;font-weight:bold;">C.3</td>
            <td style="padding:12px;border:1px solid #ddd;vertical-align:top;">Syllables & stress patterns</td>
            <td style="padding:12px;border:1px solid #ddd;vertical-align:top;">Identify word and sentence stress; mark primary stress; practise rhythm.</td>
            <td style="padding:12px;border:1px solid #ddd;vertical-align:top;">—</td>
            <td style="padding:12px;border:1px solid #ddd;vertical-align:middle;text-align:center;"><a href="notes/english/pronunciation.htm" style="color:#2c5aa0;font-weight:bold;">Check notes</a></td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td style="padding:12px;border:1px solid #ddd;vertical-align:top;font-weight:bold;">C.4</td>
            <td style="padding:12px;border:1px solid #ddd;vertical-align:top;">Rhymes, homophones & minimal pairs</td>
            <td style="padding:12px;border:1px solid #ddd;vertical-align:top;">Use minimal pairs to sharpen listening and pronunciation discrimination.</td>
            <td style="padding:12px;border:1px solid #ddd;vertical-align:top;">—</td>
            <td style="padding:12px;border:1px solid #ddd;vertical-align:middle;text-align:center;"><a href="notes/english/phonetics.htm" style="color:#2c5aa0;font-weight:bold;">Check notes</a></td>
          </tr>
          <tr style="background:#f9fdf9;">
            <td style="padding:12px;border:1px solid #ddd;vertical-align:top;font-weight:bold;">C.5</td>
            <td style="padding:12px;border:1px solid #ddd;vertical-align:top;">Intonation & sentence stress</td>
            <td style="padding:12px;border:1px solid #ddd;vertical-align:top;">Practice falling, rising and fall-rise patterns and their meanings.</td>
            <td style="padding:12px;border:1px solid #ddd;vertical-align:top;">—</td>
            <td style="padding:12px;border:1px solid #ddd;vertical-align:middle;text-align:center;"><a href="notes/english/phonetics.htm" style="color:#2c5aa0;font-weight:bold;">Check notes</a></td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td style="padding:12px;border:1px solid #ddd;vertical-align:top;font-weight:bold;">C.6</td>
            <td style="padding:12px;border:1px solid #ddd;vertical-align:top;">IPA transcription & connected speech</td>
            <td style="padding:12px;border:1px solid #ddd;vertical-align:top;">Transcribe common words; practise linking, elision and weak forms.</td>
            <td style="padding:12px;border:1px solid #ddd;vertical-align:top;">—</td>
            <td style="padding:12px;border:1px solid #ddd;vertical-align:middle;text-align:center;"><a href="notes/english/phonetics.htm" style="color:#2c5aa0;font-weight:bold;">Check notes</a></td>
          </tr>

          <!-- Exam structure row -->
          <tr style="background:#f0f0f0;font-weight:bold;">
            <td style="padding:12px;border:1px solid #999;vertical-align:top;">EXAM</td>
            <td style="padding:12px;border:1px solid #999;vertical-align:top;">Exam Structure & Question Breakdown</td>
            <td style="padding:12px;border:1px solid #999;vertical-align:top;">Refer to the exam table below for question counts (total 60 questions).</td>
            <td style="padding:12px;border:1px solid #999;vertical-align:top;">Obinna, Tomori</td>
            <td style="padding:12px;border:1px solid #999;vertical-align:middle;text-align:center;"><a href="notes/english/exam-structure.htm" style="color:#2c5aa0;font-weight:bold;">Check notes</a></td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>

    <!-- Exam structure quick table -->
    <div style="margin-top:18px; overflow:auto;">
      <table style="width:100%;border-collapse:collapse;min-width:560px;">
        <thead>
          <tr style="background:#f8f9fa;"><th style="padding:10px;border:1px solid #e6e6e6;text-align:left;">Section</th><th style="padding:10px;border:1px solid #e6e6e6;text-align:left;">Topic</th><th style="padding:10px;border:1px solid #e6e6e6;text-align:left;">Number of Questions</th></tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td style="padding:8px;border:1px solid #eee;">A</td><td style="padding:8px;border:1px solid #eee;">Comprehension passage</td><td style="padding:8px;border:1px solid #eee;">5</td></tr>
          <tr><td style="padding:8px;border:1px solid #eee;">A</td><td style="padding:8px;border:1px solid #eee;">Cloze passage</td><td style="padding:8px;border:1px solid #eee;">10</td></tr>
          <tr><td style="padding:8px;border:1px solid #eee;">A</td><td style="padding:8px;border:1px solid #eee;">Reading text</td><td style="padding:8px;border:1px solid #eee;">10</td></tr>
          <tr><td style="padding:8px;border:1px solid #eee;">B</td><td style="padding:8px;border:1px solid #eee;">Sentence interpretation</td><td style="padding:8px;border:1px solid #eee;">5</td></tr>
          <tr><td style="padding:8px;border:1px solid #eee;">B</td><td style="padding:8px;border:1px solid #eee;">Antonyms</td><td style="padding:8px;border:1px solid #eee;">5</td></tr>
          <tr><td style="padding:8px;border:1px solid #eee;">B</td><td style="padding:8px;border:1px solid #eee;">Synonyms</td><td style="padding:8px;border:1px solid #eee;">5</td></tr>
          <tr><td style="padding:8px;border:1px solid #eee;">B</td><td style="padding:8px;border:1px solid #eee;">Sentence completion</td><td style="padding:8px;border:1px solid #eee;">10</td></tr>
          <tr><td style="padding:8px;border:1px solid #eee;">C</td><td style="padding:8px;border:1px solid #eee;">Oral forms</td><td style="padding:8px;border:1px solid #eee;">10</td></tr>
          <tr style="font-weight:bold;"><td style="padding:8px;border:1px solid #eee;">Total</td><td style="padding:8px;border:1px solid #eee;"></td><td style="padding:8px;border:1px solid #eee;">60</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>

    <!-- Recommended texts list -->
    <div style="margin-top:20px;">
      <h2>Recommended Texts</h2>
      <p>Selected titles recommended for Use of English preparation:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Attah, M. O. — Practice in Spoken English for Intermediate and Advanced Learners</li>
        <li>Bamgbose, A. — English Lexis and Structure</li>
        <li>Banjo, A. et al. — New Oxford Secondary English Course</li>
        <li>Caesar, O. J. — Essential Oral English for Schools and Colleges</li>
        <li>Daniel Jones — Cambridge English Pronouncing Dictionary</li>
        <li>Obinna, M. F. — University Matriculation Use of English</li>
        <li>Tomori, S. H. O — Objective Tests for School Certificate English</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <!-- Subtopic check-notes (concise study checklist per section) -->
    <div style="margin-top:22px;">
      <h2>Study Checklists (Quick)</h2>
      <p>Use these checklists to guide revision for each section of the Use of English paper.</p>

      <h3>SECTION A — Comprehension & Summary</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Find the main idea and supporting points in each paragraph.</li>
        <li>Underline topic sentences and transitional phrases.</li>
        <li>Annotate unfamiliar words and infer meaning from context.</li>
        <li>Identify writer's tone, purpose, and stance.</li>
        <li>Practice summarising passages in your own words within the word limit.</li>
        <li>Practice cloze strategies: collocations, prepositions and verb forms.</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>SECTION B — Lexis & Structure (Quick checks)</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Synonyms/Antonyms: check register and collocation before selecting.</li>
        <li>Word formation: recognise roots, prefixes and suffixes to guess meanings.</li>
        <li>Sentence completion: test each option for grammar and sense.</li>
        <li>Concord & Tenses: ensure subject-verb agreement and correct aspect.</li>
        <li>Punctuation: look for commas, colons and semicolons that affect meaning.</li>
        <li>Sentence transformation: maintain meaning while changing structure.</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>SECTION C — Oral Forms (Quick checks)</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Recognise vowel and consonant sounds (minimal pairs practice).</li>
        <li>Identify syllable stress and word stress patterns.</li>
        <li>Practice IPA transcription for common exam words.</li>
        <li>Note intonation patterns: statements, questions, lists and contrastive stress.</li>
        <li>Practice connected speech: linking, elision and weak forms.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

